column5: Hey guys, going to be in scarborough tomorrow and wanted to try a river, are there any down that way still ice free? Thanks!

I don't know about the GTA, but i know that there is about 4 or 5 km's of open water on the trent up river from me.. if you are ever out in Quinte area feel free to give me a message, i'm always up for open water winter fishing lol.. i had the 14' aluminum and 9.9 in the water up til a week & a half ago when we got first ice. Good luck in Scarb.
Highland creek was frozen this morning so I bet most of the others  are as well.
Time to put that new to you auger to work!!.Spring will be hear soon enough.
A little birdie spoke to me today. I,ll know better friday evening.   :devil:  :devil:
